    "locked": false,
    "maintainer_can_modify": true,
    "title": "blockstorage: keep assumeutxo base block in normal blockfile range",
    "user": {
      "login": "shuv-amp",
      "id": 63120087,
      "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjYzMTIwMDg3",
      "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/63120087?v=4",
      "gravatar_id": "",
      "url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp",
      "html_url": "https://github.com/shuv-amp",
      "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/followers",
      "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/following%7B/other_user%7D",
      "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/gists%7B/gist_id%7D",
      "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/starred%7B/owner%7D%7B/repo%7D",
      "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/subscriptions",
      "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/orgs",
      "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/repos",
      "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/events%7B/privacy%7D",
      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/shuv-amp/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "An assumeutxo snapshot base block can be stored before `loadtxoutset()` sets\r\n`BlockManager::m_snapshot_height`. In that case the block is written through\r\nthe normal blockfile cursor.\r\n\r\nAfter the snapshot is loaded, the same height was classified as `ASSUMED`.\r\nIf background validation later connected that already-stored base block,\r\n`WriteBlockUndo()` could look up an `ASSUMED` blockfile cursor even though\r\nno block above the snapshot base had been written yet.\r\n\r\nThis makes the boundary exclusive: only blocks above the snapshot base height\r\nuse the `ASSUMED` blockfile range. The chainstate flush path now receives\r\nwhether it is flushing a snapshot chainstate, so a snapshot chainstate at the\r\nbase height can still return without flushing an uninitialized `ASSUMED`\r\ncursor.\r\n\r\nThe functional test stores the snapshot base block before loading the\r\nsnapshot, then feeds the missing historical blocks and checks that background\r\nvalidation completes.\r\n\r\nTested:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ntest/functional/feature_assumeutxo.py --configfile=$PWD/build/test/config.ini --timeout-factor=4",
